<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="337" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1127,940,1539]" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,262,940,963]" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1855" box="[269,529,940,963]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dolichotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bohemanii">
<emphasis box="[269,529,940,963]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Dolichotoma bohemanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remained an enigmatic taxon to subsequent workers of Cassidinae since its description. I have found a single specimen in the BMNH which possesses the original label handwritten by Guérin and in my opinion it is part of the 
<typeStatus box="[1006,1052,1004,1027]" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">type</typeStatus>
series. GUÉRIN- MÉNEVILLE (1855) did not state how many specimens he had at his disposal nor mentioned 
<typeStatus box="[224,270,1068,1091]" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">type</typeStatus>
locality. There is ‘Quixos’ written on the label what refers to the river Quijos and surrounding canton of the same name, in the Province of 
<collectingRegion box="[753,811,1100,1123]" country="Ecuador" name="Napo" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Napo</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[843,934,1100,1123]" name="Ecuador" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. Gaetano Osculati travelled through the canton from 
<date box="[512,764,1132,1155]" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" value="1847-06" valueMax="1847-11-31" valueMin="1847-06-00">June to November 1847</date>
and visited numerous places from small settlements to principal villages (e.g. Baeza and Cosanga) (
<bibRefCitation author="OSCULATI" box="[838,996,1164,1187]" firstAuthor="OSCULATI" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" refId="ref50034" refString="OSCULATI G. 1854: Esplorazione delle regione equatoriali lungo il Napo ed il fiume delle Amazzoni frammento di un viaggio fatto nelle due Americhe negli anni 1846 - 47 - 48. Fratelli Centenari E Comp., Milano, xiii + 344 pp. + 15 pls." type="book" year="1854">OSCULATI 1854</bibRefCitation>
) but it is not possible to determine where exactly he collected the specimen. I specify the 
<typeStatus box="[966,1012,1196,1219]" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">type</typeStatus>
locality as Quijos Canton according to the label data.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1127,940,1539]" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">
The 
<typeStatus box="[228,311,1260,1283]" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">syntype</typeStatus>
has simply marginate elytra and thus belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat, 1836" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[806,1126,1260,1283]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Discomorpha" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[806,951,1260,1283]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Discomorpha</emphasis>
Chevrolat, 1836
</taxonomicName>
not to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1833" box="[214,330,1292,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyclosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,330,1292,1315]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Cyclosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has doubly marginate elytra. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Guerin-Meneville" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[704,961,1292,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Discomorpha" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="bohemanii">
<emphasis box="[704,961,1292,1315]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Discomorpha bohemanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by uniformly black dorsum with dark metallic blue lustre, stout body and nearly semicircular pronotum. These characters are identical to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1920" box="[619,882,1356,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oxynodera" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="heikertingeri">
<emphasis box="[619,882,1356,1379]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Oxynodera heikertingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from Macas and thus I synonymize it with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Guerin-Meneville" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[474,620,1388,1411]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Discomorpha" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="bohemanii">
<emphasis box="[474,620,1388,1411]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">D. bohemanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1127,940,1539]" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">
<bibRefCitation author="GEMMINGER &amp; HAROLD" box="[181,501,1420,1443]" firstAuthor="GEMMINGER" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" pagination="3479 - 3822" refId="ref49433" refString="GEMMINGER M. &amp; HAROLD E. VON 1876: Catalogus Coleopterorum hucusque descriptorum synonymicus et systematicus. Tom. XII. Chrysomelidae (Pars II.), Languridae, Erotylidae, Endomychidae, Coccinelidae, Corylophidae, Platypsyllidae. Accedit index generum universalis. Theodor Ackermann, Monachii, pp. 3479 - 3822 + lxxiii." type="book chapter" year="1876">GEMMINGER &amp; HAROLD (1876)</bibRefCitation>
listed Ega (= Tefé in Amazonas, 
<collectingCountry box="[862,929,1420,1443]" name="Brazil" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) as distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Guerin-Meneville" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[151,296,1452,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Discomorpha" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="bohemanii">
<emphasis box="[151,296,1452,1475]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">D. bohemanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the information was repeated. However, it is most likely result of an error because 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Guerin-Meneville" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[242,388,1484,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Discomorpha" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="337" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="bohemanii">
<emphasis box="[242,388,1484,1507]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">D. bohemanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to eastern slopes of the Andes in 
<collectingCountry box="[876,967,1484,1507]" name="Ecuador" pageId="62" pageNumber="337">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
